FG-361 — “One Slide” Outcome Map (Pins → Order → Scope)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: A single slide can drive the signature: two pins → two-line order → scope line.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Build one landscape page with four zones: Pins (2), Order (2 lines), Scope (who/what/when), Status date. Hash and file as a notice if policy allows.
	•	📝 Assignment: Export an outcome slide for your live motion (PDF, hashed).
	•	✅ Model Response: “Pins: Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2. Order: remand 21d (a–d). Scope: ¶3 parties only; status 14d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Vision beats volume.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A slide with four boxes, ending in a small signature strip.

⸻

FG-362 — Ten-Line OA Script (Ask • Std • Pins • Relief)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Script 10 lines you can say under pressure; memorize cadence.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Lines 1–2 (ask/standard), 3–6 (two pins with short parentheticals), 7–9 (relief ladder), 10 (scope guard).
	•	📝 Assignment: Write your 10-line script; rehearse to 60–75 seconds.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Abuse; wrong test. Pins: Dkt 18:2 (harm not reached); Tab 3 p.2 (cost). Relief: reverse or remand 21d; scope ¶3 only.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Rhythm is retention.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Ten numbered bars with the last two glowing.

⸻

FG-363 — “Clock Table” Footer (Trigger • Interval • Due • Roll)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put the math at the bottom of the page—every time dates matter.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One-line footer: Trigger → +Interval → Due → Weekend/Holiday roll (local time). Repeat the same format across filings.
	•	📝 Assignment: Add a clock footer to your draft and OA card.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Rule 58 08/15 → +30 → 09/14 → weekend → 09/15 (11:59 PM local).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Math ends quibbles.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A slim bottom bar with a tiny calendar chip.

⸻

FG-364 — “No-Drama” Reconsideration (Single Gap • Two Pins)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Reconsideration wins when it fixes one pinpointed error—fast.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Quote the line; show two pins; propose one-sentence fix; “no schedule change.” Keep to ≤500–800 words by rule.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line reconsideration skeleton for a misread footnote.
	•	✅ Model Response: “p.12 n.3 ‘reached harm’ → ‘not reached’ (Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2). Clarify; no schedule impact.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Surgical > sweeping.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A pencil icon hovering over a single footnote line.

⸻

FG-365 — Page-Budget Layout (Facts 1 • Law 2 • Order 1)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Allocate pages before you write; make facts serve pins.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: 1 page Facts (pin-only), 2 pages Law (SoR + split map), 1 page Order (ladder + scope + prejudice).
	•	📝 Assignment: Paste a 4-line page budget at the top of your draft.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Facts 1p; Law 2p; Order 1p; figures/tables in addendum.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Form forces focus.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A 4-block layout; last block labeled “ORDER”.

⸻

FG-366 — Table-First Addendum (Texts • Sources • Hash)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put texts in tables—rule line, source, capture, hash.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Addendum rows: Provision • Source (official) • Capture date • SHA-256; one sentence on relevance; no evidence pages here.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 6-row text table with capture/hash footer.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Rule 65(b) — official site — captured 08/19 — SHA-256 …; relevance: emergency standard.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Tables travel; prose stalls.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A clean table with a fingerprint footer.

⸻

FG-367 — Relief Ladder Card (Primary • Alternate • Minimal • Scope)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: One 2×2 card can replace a page of prose.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Primary (decide), Alternate (limited remand), Minimal (clarify), Scope (who/what/when). Mirror the card in OA packet.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft your ladder card with exact pins in the margin.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Primary: reverse (Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2). Alt: remand 21d. Minimal: clarify n.3. Scope: ¶3 parties only; sunset 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Cards get signed.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A 2×2 grid with a small signature line below.

⸻

FG-368 — Data-to-Table Conversion (Kill the Chart Fight)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: If the chart will be argued, lead with the table.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Put the counts/dates in a table with source pins and a hash; chart becomes a visual after the table. Cite the table, not the chart.
	•	📝 Assignment: Convert one chart page to a one-page table and cite it.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Days pending by motion (official dockets, captured 08/19; SHA-256 …).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Tables end “looks misleading” fights.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A chart fading behind a crisp table.

⸻

FG-369 — Limited-Remand Block (Task • Time • Scope • Fallback)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Write the four-line block that returns a clean record.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Task (findings on a–d) • Time (21–30d) • Scope (no expansion) • Fallback (20-min harm hearing). Paste into conclusion and OA.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft your four lines in neutral voice; no adjectives.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Remand to enter findings on (a)–(d) within 21 days; scope limited; 20-minute harm-only hearing; status ≤3 pp on return.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Instruction is persuasion.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Four labeled tiles connected to an “ORDER” bar.

⸻

FG-370 — After-Order Micro-Status (Facts • Two Dates • Ask)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Post-order, return with facts + dates + tiny ask—in 120 words.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: What happened (one sentence + pin), two dates (rehearing/mandate/costs), and a one-line door (clarify/hold/limited remand).
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 120-word micro-status for your latest order.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Opinion issued 09/01 (pin); rehearing due 09/15; costs 09/15; ask: hold 21d or remand 21d for harm findings.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Small notes move calendars; big ones stall them.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A slim paragraph with two calendar chips and a tiny order line.